---
# ============================================================
# Pod Security Standards (PSS) — cluster baseline admission control
# ============================================================
# PSS is Kubernetes' built-in LABEL-BASED admission control (it replaced the
# PodSecurityPolicy, removed in v1.25). A Namespace labelled
#   pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce=<level>   -> REJECT pods exceeding <level>
#   pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit=<level>      -> only log them to the audit log
#   pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn=<level>       -> only warn the API caller
# Levels: privileged (no policy), baseline (blocks the real escape vectors),
# restricted (baseline + runAsNonRoot / drop ALL caps / seccomp=RuntimeDefault —
# breaks many unmodified images). The three modes can use different levels.
#
# Baseline policy applied here (both Namespaces are patched/created by this
# manifest; re-applying just re-asserts the labels — idempotent, self-healing
# across k3s restarts):
#   default       : enforce=baseline, audit=restricted, warn=restricted
#     - enforce=baseline  blocks privileged / hostPath / hostNetwork / hostPID
#       pods. `default` is the strict-quarantine namespace (see
#       11-network-policies.yml.j2): no real app belongs there, so baseline
#       breaks nothing while closing escape vectors on anything that lands there.
#     - audit+warn=restricted  log/warn (NOT block) pods that *could* be hardened
#       further, so you can migrate gradually without breakage.
#   cert-manager  : SAME (enforce=baseline, audit=restricted, warn=restricted),
#     only when certmanager_enabled. Unlike the exempt namespaces below,
#     cert-manager has NO privileged/hostNetwork/hostPath pod — controller,
#     webhook, cainjector and the OVH webhook are all plain pods, so baseline
#     breaks nothing and adds defense-in-depth on a namespace that already has
#     a deny-all NetworkPolicy (25-certmanager-network-policies.yml.j2). The
#     official cert-manager.yaml (20-) creates this namespace; this manifest
#     pre-creates it with the labels, then 20- patches it (idempotent).
#   cert-manager-infomaniak : SAME, only when certmanager_enabled AND at least
#     one Infomaniak cred is present (the same condition site.yml uses to deploy
#     the webhook). The official rendered-manifest (21-) creates this separate
#     namespace for the Infomaniak webhook; this manifest pre-creates it with the
#     labels, then 21- patches it (idempotent). The Infomaniak webhook is a
#     plain pod too, so baseline is safe there.
#   monitoring  : SAME (enforce=baseline, audit=restricted, warn=restricted), only
#     when observability_enabled. The stateful control plane (Prometheus, Grafana,
#     Loki, Alertmanager, kube-state-metrics) — all plain pods, so baseline breaks
#     nothing. Pre-created here with the labels, patched by 60-/61- (idempotent).
#     The host DaemonSets that violate baseline (node-exporter, Alloy) live in the
#     exempt `observability-host` namespace (created unlabelled below).
#   restricted is NOT enforced anywhere automatically: too many images do not
#   comply (runAsNonRoot etc.) and it would turn the baseline into friction.
#   Opt into it per sensitive namespace when you create one.
#
# Intentionally NOT labelled (= privileged, no enforcement) — these hold system
# pods that legitimately need privileged / hostNetwork and would break under
# baseline:
#   kube-system               (kube-vip, Traefik, CoreDNS, kube-proxy, metrics-server)
#   metallb-system            (speaker DaemonSet runs hostNetwork)
#   ceph-csi-operator-system  (CSI node plugins run privileged + hostNetwork)
#   observability-host        (when observability_enabled — node-exporter +
#                             Alloy use hostNetwork/hostPID/hostPath; isolated here
#                             instead of weakening baseline-enforced `monitoring`)
# An unlabelled namespace has NO PSA enforcement, which is the correct default
# for them. (K3s sets no cluster-wide default profile, so "unlabelled" is truly
# unrestricted — there is nothing to override.)
#
# Application namespaces: create them with enforce=baseline — see the README
# "Securing a new namespace" tutorial (Step 1).
# ============================================================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: default
  labels:
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce: baseline
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn-version: latest
{% if certmanager_enabled | bool %}
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: cert-manager
  labels:
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce: baseline
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn-version: latest
{% endif %}
{% if certmanager_enabled | bool and (certmanager_dns_credentials | default([]) | selectattr('provider', 'equalto', 'infomaniak') | list | length > 0) %}
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: cert-manager-infomaniak
  labels:
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce: baseline
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn-version: latest
{% endif %}
{% if observability_enabled | bool %}
---
# monitoring — baseline-enforced (pre-created here; patched by 60-/61-).
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: {{ observability_namespace }}
  labels:
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce: baseline
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit-version: latest
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn: restricted
    pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn-version: latest
---
# observability-host — UNLABELLED (exempt): host DaemonSets that violate baseline.
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: {{ observability_host_namespace }}
{% endif %}